race.comment: TIME TO BACA (5) switched from a top Victorian yard and didn't have the best of it as an odds-on favourite first up. Quickly made amends winning her Maiden and is sure to build on that. Has the inside barrier and 3kg claim and there's more up the sleeve. Stablemate SNAPPY SWEETHEART (6) is the danger seeking the hat-trick on a 2-week turnaround. Runs along and has plenty of scope for improvement. ACHACHA (7) peaks for the same yard and is busting to win. Has an awkward gate but her lip defeat two back stacks up. NO I'M NOT (3) also showed enough two back to give her a chance. She didn't have much luck the latest.
